100 Oz wagyu beef chuck. The cut portion for serving is also known as the Denver Cut Steak is Flavor-rich and super marble meat. Cooked to perfection with my @meatermade wireless ThermoMEATER+ 
.
Reverse sear method step by step:
The meat rest inside my BGE Getting more and more tenderness,  smoke and aroma from pecan wood chunks. temperature should be around 100-120 ° C. Do not go over to 150 ° C to prevent process of searing the meat. Waiting for about two hours to reach the your internal target temperature inside the meat (use temperature probs). The For me the target temperature is  about 53-54 degrees Celsius (medium-rear). the thermometers should be placed close to the bone where it is area in the steak that harder for heat penetration. At this stage let the meat a rest of 2-3 minutes and meanwhile increase the burners to the maximum heat. I go with mywood fire oven . 2 minutes of searing on each side, another 5 minutes of rest and it's ready to be your perfect steak. This is one of the only ways to achieve a same cooked and color from edge to edge by using grill only.

Crazy Ribeye steak by 📹 @vertsmoke I’m totally mouth watering 🤤 What a edge to edge perfection! Try the reverse sear method for perfect steak time after time. 
.
About Reverse seared steak - the best way to get a perfect steak side to side. Low and slow till internal temp 53C/130F Than 7 mins rest. Direct fire finish with fast burning in very high heat in my Sizzle Zone burner (2-3 mins total). 3 minutes rest before cutting.  WOW!
